article.headline: South Carolina St. 74, Hampton 63
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- After two tough conference losses last week, South Carolina State got things back on the winning track with a 74-63 victory over the Hampton on Saturday night. Forward Brian Mason led South Carolina State (7-12, 5-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) with 16 points, while Travis Jones and Derrick Davis each added 14. Rashad West had a career night for Hampton (7-12, 3-5), shooting 6-8 from the arc and finishing with 24 points, while Demario Mattox added 15. A reverse dunk by South Carolina State's Robert Baker sparked a 15-5 run over the Pirates, giving the Bulldogs their biggest lead of the game -- 66-54 -- with 1:36 to go. South Carolina State was tough down the stretch despite being tied dead even in rebounding, with 30, pulling out a much-needed conference win.
